<subSubSection id="C197CBD73172FFF0FF08FE621193FCDA" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8932985C3172FFF0FF08FE621016FD11" blockId="8.[151,1436,511,874]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="BBF9444E3172FFF0FF08FE621403FDDC" bold="true" box="[151,280,511,537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
male flagellomeres without median constriction (“unibottled”), with few ventral microcilia; A5 modified; claval formula: 1:2:2:2:1; suprahumeral and cervical pronotal sulci not foveolate; anterior tip of pronotum well developed; notaulus usually present in females, in 
<taxonomicName id="4E8DE3DF3172FFF0FC21FDD7117FFDA6" box="[958,1124,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Xenomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanharteni">
<emphasis id="BBF9444E3172FFF0FC21FDD7117FFDA6" box="[958,1124,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">X. vanharteni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
absent both in males and females; mesopleural carina incomplete; metapleural epicoxal carina absent dorsally; propodeal lateral carinae inverted V-shaped; lateral patch on T3 reduced, not extending across to the whole tergum; apical setae on T3 short; T9+T10 with two apical setae; acrosternal calices fused medially, spherical in shape.
</paragraph>
